Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.77,0:01:47.65,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,There!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.65,0:01:48.54,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.56,0:01:55.14,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Hey, got a minute?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.14,0:01:56.27,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,What? What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.27,0:01:57.48,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I know what you're thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.02,0:02:00.60,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,But, it's not that funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.48,0:02:04.19,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm not wearing these\Nto be funny or anything...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.36,0:02:07.53,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Hey, Kamiyama!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.03,0:02:09.36,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,What is it, Hayashida?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.36,0:02:11.87,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Do you wanna go grab a bite on the way home?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.87,0:02:12.87,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.87,0:02:13.87,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,See you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.87,0:02:15.16,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Hey, hold on a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.74,0:02:18.43,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Haven't you become cold these days?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.43,0:02:19.96,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Hold on a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.96,0:02:23.92,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Why do I have to be called cold\Njust because I declined a meal?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.92,0:02:25.92,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I'm simply not hungry, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.92,0:02:31.13,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,No, I think you were kinder\N and gentler when we first met.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.13,0:02:34.51,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,That's right. You've changed recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.72,0:02:37.77,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Okay. Listen carefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.77,0:02:41.60,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Just because everyone has this\Nimage of me as "gentle" or "quiet,"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.60,0:02:46.40,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,just because I seemed a little cold,\Npeople look at me as a "very cold guy."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.40,0:02:47.98,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Things like that happen all the time, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.98,0:02:50.28,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I see. I guess that might be true.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.28,0:02:51.28,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,On the other hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.28,0:02:55.45,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,just because someone who's very bad,\Nlike Hayashida, seems a little kind,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.45,0:02:58.29,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,people will think\N "Oh, Hayashida is actually a very nice guy"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.29,0:03:00.74,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,or "He was actually a kind person."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.29,0:03:04.54,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,People have illusions like that all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.54,0:03:07.75,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I think that's probably also why I seemed cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.75,0:03:08.76,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.76,0:03:09.92,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,For example,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.92,0:03:14.76,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,suppose I put my legs up on the desk like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.76,0:03:17.22,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,And you put your legs up\Nthe same way, Hayashida.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.18,0:03:20.56,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.56,0:03:22.89,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,How does this look, everyone? \NWe're doing the same thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.89,0:03:25.81,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,but for some reason,\N only I appear to be a very bad guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.81,0:03:27.23,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Oh! That's true!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.23,0:03:29.61,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Only Kamiyama appears to be\Na bad guy for some reason!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.61,0:03:32.10,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,While Hayashida just looks like\Nhe's relaxing comfortably!
Dialogue: 1,0:03:32.61,0:03:33.66,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,This time,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.10,0:03:32.94,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.4\fnAnna\shad0\bord0\c&H37331D&\fs35\frz8.74\pos(345.538,487)}Psychology
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.94,0:03:32.98,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.4\fnAnna\shad0\bord0\c&H37331D&\fs34\frz8.74\pos(354.601,482)}Psychology
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.98,0:03:33.02,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.4\fnAnna\shad0\bord0\c&H37331D&\fs31\frz8.74\pos(381.791,460)}Psychology
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.02,0:03:33.06,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.4\fnAnna\shad0\bord0\c&H37331D&\fs27\frz8.74\pos(432.772,423)}Psychology
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.02,0:03:33.06,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.4\fnAnna\shad0\bord0\c&H37331D&\fs23\frz8.74\pos(-14.728,412)}Psychology
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.06,0:03:33.10,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.4\fnAnna\shad0\bord0\c&H37331D&\fs23\frz8.74\pos(472.424,390)}Psychology
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.06,0:03:33.10,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.4\fnAnna\shad0\bord0\c&H37331D&\fs21\frz8.74\pos(107.627,381)}Psychology
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.10,0:03:33.15,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.4\fnAnna\shad0\bord0\c&H37331D&\fs21\pos(497.915,370)\frz8.74}Psychology
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.10,0:03:33.15,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.4\fnAnna\shad0\bord0\c&H37331D&\fs19\pos(177.867,362)\frz8.74}Psychology
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.15,0:03:40.57,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.4\fnAnna\shad0\bord0\c&H37331D&\fs20\pos(504.146,364)\frz8.74}Psychology
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.15,0:03:40.57,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.4\fnAnna\shad0\bord0\c&H37331D&\fs18\pos(198.259,356)\frz8.74}Psychology
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.66,0:03:36.16,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,suppose the two of us are reading, like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.16,0:03:37.66,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Doesn't it look, for some reason,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.66,0:03:40.79,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,like Hayashida's trying very hard to\Nread a book he doesn't understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.79,0:03:41.79,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.79,0:03:44.12,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Kamiyama looks like\N he's just reading it to pass time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.92,0:03:50.17,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,In summary, a person's everyday image\Ninfluences the judgment of others quite a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.17,0:03:51.34,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.34,0:03:53.80,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Moreover, the more a person's actions\Ndiffer from the everyday image,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.80,0:03:54.93,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,the stronger the impression becomes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.59,0:03:58.47,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Taking this into account,\N let's move on to the next experiment.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.47,0:03:59.60,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,What experiment?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.14,0:04:01.06,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I'll fudging kill you, you morons!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.56,0:04:03.52,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Whoa! Scary!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.52,0:04:04.48,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Very scary, Kamiyama!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.06,0:04:07.15,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,You looked so scary that I almost\Noffered you my money!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.15,0:04:08.48,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,That's going a bit too far.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.48,0:04:09.48,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,How's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.48,0:04:13.28,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,If a person who is always angry\Nbecomes angry, it's not that scary.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.28,0:04:15.95,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,But if someone who usually doesn't get angry\Nloses it once in a while, it's very scary, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.95,0:04:17.78,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Incredible! This is an incredible discovery!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.78,0:04:19.70,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Still, this is just the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.70,0:04:20.99,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,This is the most basic of basics.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.99,0:04:23.04,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,What?! Are you saying that\Nthis is just the beginning?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.04,0:04:24.25,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,What the hell's gonna happen?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.45,0:04:32.50,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\fscx96.297\blur0.5\fnAnna\shad0\bord0\c&H37331D&\fs10\pos(631.032,453)\frz0\frx330\fry20}P{\frz-2}s{\frz-3}y{\frz-5}c{\frz-8}h{\frz-10}o{\frz-12}l{\frz-14}ogy
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.50,0:04:32.54,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\fscx96.297\blur0.5\fnAnna\shad0\bord0\c&H37331D&\fs10\frz0\frx330\fry20\pos(641.228,463)}P{\frz-2}s{\frz-3}y{\frz-5}c{\frz-8}h{\frz-10}o{\frz-12}l{\frz-14}ogy
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.79,0:04:28.33,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,The reason why Hayashida\N looked like he was "trying very hard"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.33,0:04:30.59,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,was because he's a stranger to books.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.59,0:04:32.55,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Due to that, it was more effective.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.55,0:04:35.43,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,But, then, what happens if it's someone\Nwho's even more of a stranger to books?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.76,0:04:36.76,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,And so...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.76,0:04:37.80,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Enter Gorilla.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.72,0:04:42.85,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,This time, we'll have Hayashida and Gorilla\Nsit next to each other and read.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.85,0:04:46.10,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Now which one looks like he's trying harder?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.10,0:04:49.06,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,What?! This time Gorilla's the one\Nthat looks like he's trying harder!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.06,0:04:49.61,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.61,0:04:51.85,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Or rather, hasn't this conversation\Ntaken a strange turn?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.85,0:04:53.40,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I-Incredible...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.40,0:04:56.56,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Hayashida looked like he was trying hard earlier,\Nbut he looks like he's well-read this time!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.11,0:04:58.87,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,If it's this effective,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.87,0:05:01.41,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,we may be able to apply it to other things.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.41,0:05:04.37,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Good point. Then let's move onto the next step.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.37,0:05:05.58,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,There's more?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.58,0:05:08.82,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,First, have Gorilla hold a banana as usual.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.25,0:05:10.59,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,That's normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.59,0:05:12.55,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,That's a familiar sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.55,0:05:13.76,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,That's normal, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.76,0:05:15.75,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Then shall I switch the banana with a mike?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.51,0:05:21.14,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Now from your viewpoint, who looks like\Nhe has better singing ability, me or Gorilla?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.47,0:05:23.97,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Gorilla looks like a better singer!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.97,0:05:25.88,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Incredible! It's like he sings with vibrato!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.39,0:05:27.94,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,It's just like magic...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.94,0:05:31.37,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,This is without doubt a technique that cleverly\Ntakes advantage of the depths of the psyche...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.86,0:05:33.65,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Then, this is the last step.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.65,0:05:35.33,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,It's a test to check human judgment.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.69,0:05:37.36,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,What? Are you going to do more?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.36,0:05:39.32,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I'll go ahead and wear a sash across my chest.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.32,0:05:41.53,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,And l'll put another sash on Gorilla, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.95,0:05:43.83,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,And each of us hold a mike.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.83,0:05:44.87,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.87,0:05:45.29,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Now...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.83,0:05:47.43,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Which one will you vote for?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.24,0:05:47.41,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\an1\fnArial\fs22\shad0\c&H181715&\3c&HEDECE5&\bord2\be2\pos(11.329,445)}Your vote \Nwill change politics\N-Takashi Kamiyama
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.24,0:05:47.41,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\an3\fnArial\fs22\shad0\c&H181715&\3c&HEDECE5&\bord2\be2\pos(702.405,445)}Please give me\N your vote{\i1}!!{\i0}\N-Gorilla
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.62,0:05:48.96,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,We'll vote for Gorilla!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.46,0:05:50.93,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,No, we won't, we won't.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.91,0:05:54.33,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.4\pos(463.361,350)\fnAnna\bord0\shad0\fs16\c&H191713&}Ballot\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\NBox
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.46,0:05:53.34,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,For one thing, you guys don't have voting rights.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.21,0:05:56.21,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,So, as you can see,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.21,0:05:58.29,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,it's not that I've become cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.47,0:06:01.05,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,No, you've definitely changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.05,0:06:04.81,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,That's right. You used to be more polite\Nor maybe I should say quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.81,0:06:08.73,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Geez, you still don't understand after\NI went through all that explanation?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.73,0:06:10.40,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,All right, then. That's enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.40,0:06:12.56,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Indeed, I might have changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.56,0:06:15.44,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,But you can't say that "changing"\Nis a bad thing with absolute certainty.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.82,0:06:18.88,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Rather, without change there is no progress!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.88,0:06:20.99,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.99,0:06:23.12,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,But not changing has its merits too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.12,0:06:24.58,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,How should I say it,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.58,0:06:27.91,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,with some things,\N it's a relief if they don't change...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.91,0:06:29.33,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,There are, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.33,0:06:32.75,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Oh, of course, I do also see\Nthe merits of not changing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.75,0:06:36.46,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,The disposition of refusing to change. \NSuch a policy is also wonderful in a sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.17,0:06:41.47,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,It' like a "how long do you plan on using that material?" question for once-famous comedians.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.47,0:06:44.49,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Just to be clear, I definitely\N don't mean to make fun of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.01,0:06:47.68,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,In short, I respect both ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.68,0:06:49.93,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,It doesn't mean either attitude is bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.93,0:06:51.85,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Hmm, that's kind of a pain.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.85,0:06:57.14,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,For example, a high school girl who used to be very serious can suddenly dye her hair after summer vacation ends.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.14,0:06:59.19,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that happens sometimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.19,0:07:02.32,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,And it makes a big shock\N for a lot of the male students.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.70,0:07:05.53,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,And they start whispering and gossiping\Namongst each other and stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.53,0:07:08.87,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Like "she did something with such and such a person." That's not good, you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.87,0:07:11.54,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Well, then should we ignore it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.54,0:07:14.16,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Then she'd feel lonely, being treated as an outsider.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.58,0:07:19.63,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I'm sure planning such a big change in image means that she has some level of assertiveness and preparedness.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.50,0:07:21.17,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\fad(500,0)\pos(566.456,38)\shad0\blur0.4\bord0\c&H70DBF6&\fs22\fnComplete in Him}Challenger
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.92,0:07:21.19,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,In a sense she's a challenger!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.72,0:07:25.47,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I'd like to cheer on such a challenger\Nfrom the bottom of my heart!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.47,0:07:28.31,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,It certainly takes a lot of guts\Nto change your image!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.31,0:07:31.06,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,All right! Why don't we\N support someone like that too?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.06,0:07:33.06,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,YEAH!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.06,0:07:34.43,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,It's very hard to go in there now...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.10,0:07:37.23,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,The Year 1 Boss at Destrade High School,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.35,0:07:43.19,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\an1\be2\pos(96.297,345)}Destrade High School Year 1 Boss\N Noboru Yamaguchi (Pen Name - Ajishio Taro)
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.23,0:07:40.49,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,{\pos(358,478)}Noboru Yamaguchi, also known\Nby his pen name Ajishio Taro,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.49,0:07:44.15,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,{\pos(358,478)}was a little upbeat because the postcard\Nhe sent in was read in a radio show.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.15,0:07:45.70,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I'm hungry, Yamaguchi, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.40,0:07:47.44,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\be2\pos(402.184,356)}Destrade High School Year 1
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.40,0:07:47.44,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\an3\be2\pos(347.804,428)}Jun Ishikawa
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.70,0:07:47.74,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Shall we go out for some food? I'll treat you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.74,0:07:49.08,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,What? Are you serious, Yamaguchi?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.08,0:07:50.41,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Yeah, don't be modest.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.41,0:07:52.87,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I'll treat you to sushi or whatever you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.87,0:07:56.88,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Yamaguchi also got some prize money\Nbecause his postcard was read.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.88,0:07:57.88,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Then let's go for sushi.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.88,0:07:59.53,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,You don't pull any punches, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.54,0:08:01.54,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.4\fnOneDirection\fs62\b0\c&H27262D&\shad0\bord0\frx8\fry8\frz359\pos(355.734,350)}Sushi
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.95,0:08:01.34,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I haven't had sushi in a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.80,0:08:04.01,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Well, eat as much as you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.76,0:08:19.68,Typeset,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.4\fnOneDirection\fs48\b0\c&H27262D&\shad0\bord0\frx8\fry8\frz357\pos(300.222,157)}Sushi
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.10,0:08:11.31,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,What? Did something happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.31,0:08:14.14,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Well... I just wondered if this\Nis really a sushi restaurant...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.14,0:08:17.27,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Hey, Yamaguchi, this is definitely a sushi restaurant. Look at the sign.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.27,0:08:19.71,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Well, it's 100% true the sign is\Nfor a sushi restaurant, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.02,0:08:22.24,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about it! Let's go in. I'm hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.24,0:08:22.99,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.74,0:08:28.91,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Hey, is this place open?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.91,0:08:31.41,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Isn't it possible that they're\Ngetting ready to open?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.41,0:08:32.95,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Huh? What're you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.95,0:08:36.04,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Oh, I got it. Suddenly you felt like treating me was a waste, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.04,0:08:37.46,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,You can't back out now!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.46,0:08:39.88,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Hey, chief! Could you make me\Nwhatever sushi you recommend?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.92,0:08:42.80,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Oh, gizzard shad? That's trendy!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.67,0:08:47.97,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Yeah, the fish is fresh and the\Nmarinade is well done too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.97,0:08:49.70,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,There's nothing to complain about.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.76,0:08:51.85,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Hey, it's a gorilla!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.85,0:08:53.32,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Took you long enough to notice!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.32,0:08:54.43,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Wait a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.43,0:08:55.98,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,That double take he just did...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.98,0:08:57.65,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,He's pretty good!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.65,0:08:59.77,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Just what you'd expect from\None of my subordinates.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.77,0:09:02.40,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,His sense of humor has improved!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.40,0:09:05.53,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I should recognize Ishikawa a little more...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.53,0:09:06.61,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,You've improved!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.61,0:09:09.11,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about?! \NIt's a gorilla! Let's get the hell out!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.66,0:09:12.41,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Listen, Ishikawa. Calm down\N and think about it carefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.41,0:09:16.27,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,"A gorilla at a sushi restaurant"... You don't encounter such an interesting situation very often!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.66,0:09:19.00,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Well, even if you say it's interesting...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.00,0:09:22.92,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Look. There are only about two restaurants\Nlike this even if you look all over the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.92,0:09:24.41,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,This is an incredible restaurant, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.88,0:09:26.51,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Well, that's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.51,0:09:30.51,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,If the gorilla was just in here, it wouldn't be that big of a deal, but the gorilla is making sushi, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.51,0:09:34.06,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Well, if you're with me, you come\Nacross interesting stuff like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.06,0:09:36.02,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,After all, the god of comedy is with me...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.02,0:09:38.52,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,In any case, why is there a gorilla making sushi?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.52,0:09:40.19,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Well, I know why.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.19,0:09:41.62,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,What?! You do, Yamaguchi?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.32,0:09:47.32,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,One day when there was snow and sleet, this gorilla was probably standing in front of the restaurant.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.70,0:09:50.62,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,The restaurant owner,\N who couldn't just stand by, let him in...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.62,0:09:53.28,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,thinking that even for a gorilla,\Nit's hard to be out in this cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.74,0:09:55.66,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Why was a gorilla in front of the restaurant?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.66,0:09:57.48,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,How should I know, idiot?! It doesn't matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.48,0:10:01.04,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Anyway, he let the gorilla stay inside\Nthe restaurant, treating him like a pet.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.04,0:10:03.88,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Seeing him beside the chef\Nwould be a peaceful sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.88,0:10:06.09,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,But all that gorilla chow cost a pretty penny!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.09,0:10:09.09,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,The owner had to work extra hard \Nand was struck down by an illness.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.09,0:10:10.54,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,That's pretty dramatic...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.84,0:10:13.55,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,"I wanna help the restaurant owner\Nwho took good care of me somehow..."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.55,0:10:15.47,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,The gorilla would think in his own way.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.47,0:10:18.85,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,He tried watching and imitating\Nthe other chefs, but he was just a gorilla.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.85,0:10:20.85,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,There was no way he could make sushi properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.85,0:10:23.98,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,But without showing\N the slightest sign of those thoughts,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.98,0:10:27.90,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I'd imagine the owner would eat the gorilla's\Npoorly made sushi as if it was really good.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.57,0:10:30.66,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,The restaurant owner would surely think...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.66,0:10:34.91,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,"Why do they discriminate against gorillas?\NWhat's wrong with a gorilla making sushi?"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.91,0:10:35.63,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.87,0:10:39.50,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Oh, look. That restaurant owner is finally here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.79,0:10:42.38,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Oh, no! There's a gorilla in the restaurant!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.92,0:10:43.58,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,{\c&HB7D2DC&}He was here without permission?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.58,0:10:45.02,Dialogue etc,,0,0,0,,Of course he was...
